From f84a00190000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrew Miller <soc1024@illinois.edu>
Date: Mon, 31 Mar 2026 20:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Deterministic inference: full CPU-GPU bitwise parity

26 divergence fixes across transcendentals, FMA, quantization, attention,
RoPE, cumsum, and GDN. Includes dp4a MMQ kernel (shelved for 27B),
unified runtime toggle, q4_0 KV shadow, and det-diag tooling.

Verified models (RTX 3090 SM86 / CUDA 12.8):
- Qwen2.5-3B Q4_K_M, Llama-3.2-3B IQ4_XS, Qwen3.5-4B IQ4_XS,
  Qwen3.5-27B IQ4_XS — all tensors match bitwise GPU-to-CPU.

Commits squashed:
- 16e0ecd1 CPU-GPU bitwise parity: standard transformers + Qwen3.5 hybrid Mamba
- f74af997 Unified deterministic build: runtime mode, q4_0 KV shadow, GDN CPU parity
- e49087fd Full CPU-GPU parity for long prompts: mmvq dispatch + cumsum + nwarps fix
- dc4b86fa dp4a MMQ kernel for deterministic prefill: 5x speedup with full CPU parity
- 55a08506 Revert dp4a mmq dispatch: slower than mmvq-4col for 27B models
- f84a0019 docs: update det-diag README to project status (shelved)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
