+# Stock vs Deterministic Tensor Comparison — 2026-03-30
+
+## Setup
+- GPU: RTX 3090 (SM86)
+- Builds: `build-stock-diag` (GGML_DETERMINISTIC=OFF) vs `build-det-real` (GGML_DETERMINISTIC=ON)
+- Both from `deterministic-v2` branch (commit 16e0ecd1)
+- Prompt: "The quick brown fox", seed=42, temp=0.7, n=3
+
+## Results
+
+| Model | Type | Quant | Match | Differ | Tokens Match? |
+|-------|------|-------|-------|--------|---------------|
+| Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct | standard transformer | IQ4_XS | 3500/3500 (100%) | 0 | yes |
+| Qwen2.5-3B | standard transformer | Q4_K_M | 4924/4924 (100%) | 0 | yes |
+| Qwen3.5-4B (heretic) | hybrid Mamba + SSM | IQ4_XS | 368/7332 (5%) | 6964 | yes (by luck) |
+
+## Key Finding
+
+**Standard transformers**: Stock CUDA math (`expf`, `rsqrtf`, `sinf`) produces **bitwise identical**
+results to portable math (`expf_det`, `sincosf_det`, etc.) on RTX 3090 SM86. The `#ifdef GGML_DETERMINISTIC`
+kernel guards change the code path but not the output. Zero divergence across all tensors.
+
+**Hybrid Mamba/SSM**: 95% tensor divergence. SSM conv, gated-delta-net, and related ops genuinely differ
+between stock and deterministic math. Tensor dimensions also differ (e.g., `8192×4` vs `128×128`),
+suggesting different kernel dispatch/layout, not just ULP differences.
+
+## Implications
+
+1. For standard transformers on SM86, the entire speed gap comes from **host-side dispatch**
+   (serialized MoE matmul, mmvq-only, fattn-vec-only), not from kernel math.
+
+2. The portable math functions are effectively free on this GPU — they produce the same bits
+   as the hardware SFU instructions. This may not hold on other architectures (A100, H100).
+
+3. For MoE/Mamba models, the kernel-level deterministic math IS load-bearing.
+
+## CPU-GPU Parity (verified)
+
+| Model | GPU tensors | CPU tensors | Match | Tokens |
+|-------|-------------|-------------|-------|--------|
+| Qwen2.5-3B Q4_K_M | 4924 | 4924 | 4924/4924 (100%) | identical |
+
+GPU build: `build-det-real` with `-DGGML_DETERMINISTIC=ON`, `GGML_DETERMINISTIC=1` env
+CPU build: `build-det-cpu` (no compile flag, runtime `GGML_DETERMINISTIC=1` only)
+Prompt: "The quick brown fox", seed=42, temp=0.7, n=3
+
+**CPU verification works.** Anyone can reproduce GPU output on a CPU for this model.
+
+## Speed Overhead (qwen2.5-3b Q4_K_M, llama-server, 3 runs each)
+
+| Mode | tok/s |
+|------|-------|
+| Stock | 213, 224, 233 |
+| Deterministic | 207, 234, 234 |
+
+**~0% overhead** — within noise for standard transformers on SM86.
+
+## TODO
+- Test on 27B dense model (same architecture family — expect same result)
+- Test MoE models (Qwen3-Coder 30B A3B) — expect divergence from MoE dispatch
+- Test cross-session determinism (restart server, same seed → same output?)
