+++ b/tools/det-diag/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,103 @@
+# Deterministic Inference — Project Status
+
+CPU-GPU bitwise parity for llama.cpp on RTX 3090 (SM86).
+GPU produces output, CPU can verify every tensor matches exactly.
+
+## Status: Shelved
+
+Works, but too slow for daily use. The 27B model drops from ~1385 tok/s prefill
+(stock MMA) to 129 tok/s (deterministic mmvq-4col) — a 10× penalty.
+Generation speed is unaffected but prefill latency makes it impractical for
+interactive use at 27B scale.
+
+## What works
+
+- **26 divergence fixes** across transcendentals, FMA, quantization, attention, RoPE, cumsum, GDN
+- **5 models verified** bitwise CPU-GPU match: Qwen2.5-3B Q4_K_M, Llama-3.2-3B IQ4_XS, Qwen3.5-4B IQ4_XS, Qwen3.5-27B IQ4_XS, Qwen3.5-4B heretic
+- **Unified build** — single binary, runtime `GGML_DETERMINISTIC=1` toggles det mode
+- **dp4a MMQ kernel** — 5× faster than mmvq for small models (3B: 642 tok/s), but slower for 27B (86 vs 129)
+- **Docker verifier** — anyone with the model file can reproduce GPU output on CPU
+
+## Performance (llama-bench pp512, 27B IQ4_XS)
+
+| Mode | Prefill tok/s | Why |
+|------|--------------|-----|
+| Stock (MMA tensor cores) | 1385 | hardware matmul |
+| Det mmvq-4col (current) | 129 | per-column dot products, no weight reuse |
+| Det dp4a MMQ | 86 | tiled but integer ALU can't keep up at 27B scale |
+
+Small models (3B) have no meaningful penalty — dp4a MMQ hits 642 tok/s vs ~6000 stock.
+
+## The bottleneck
+
+Matmul is 97% of det prefill time. Stock llama.cpp uses MMA tensor cores for
+matmul — these are a black box whose accumulation can't be reproduced on CPU.
+Det mode falls back to mmvq (one column at a time, dp4a integer ALU), which is
+10× slower for large weight matrices.
+
+The dp4a MMQ kernel tiles weights in shared memory (like stock mmq) but uses
+integer ALU instead of tensor cores. This helps small models (shmem reuse
+dominates) but not 27B (compute throughput dominates).
+
+## Builds
+
+```bash
+# Unified build (GPU + CPU, runtime det toggle)
+cmake -B build-unified -DGGML_CUDA=ON -DGGML_CPU_REPACK=ON
+cmake --build build-unified -j$(nproc)
+
+# Run with deterministic mode
+GGML_DETERMINISTIC=1 build-unified/bin/llama-server \
+  -m model.gguf -ngl 99 --flash-attn
+
+# CPU-only verifier (minimal flags for portability)
+cmake -B build-verify \
+  -DGGML_CUDA=OFF -DGGML_CPU_REPACK=OFF -DGGML_LLAMAFILE=OFF \
+  -DGGML_NATIVE=OFF -DGGML_AVX2=OFF -DGGML_AVX=OFF \
+  -DGGML_FMA=OFF -DGGML_F16C=OFF \
+  -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-mfma" -DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS="-mfma"
+cmake --build build-verify --target llama-det-diag -j$(nproc)
+```
+
+## Key files
+
+| File | What |
+|------|------|
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cuda/mmq-det.cu` | dp4a MMQ kernel (#undef MMA trick) |
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cpu/quants.c` | CPU shadow dot products (mmvq + mmq) |
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cpu/ggml-cpu.c` | det dispatch (det_vec_dot, det_from_float) |
+| `ggml/src/ggml-quants.c` | quantize_row_q8_1_mmq (GPU-matching quantization) |
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu` | matmul dispatch (mmvq-4col for det) |
+| `tools/det-diag/det-diag.cpp` | tensor-level hash comparison tool |
+| `tools/det-diag/verify.sh` | end-to-end seed verification script |
+
+## Commits
+
+- `16e0ecd1` — initial CPU-GPU parity (standard transformers + Mamba)
+- `f74af997` — unified build, runtime toggle, q4_0 KV shadow, GDN parity
+- `e49087fd` — long-prompt fixes (mmvq dispatch, cumsum, nwarps)
+- `dc4b86fa` — dp4a MMQ kernel + CPU shadow (verified bitwise)
+- `55a08506` — reverted dp4a dispatch (slower for 27B), code preserved
+
+## What would make it usable
+
+1. **Faster GPU without tensor cores** — dp4a occupancy improvements (fix shmem waste), stream-k scheduling, or a custom tiled kernel
+2. **Probabilistic verification** — e.g. Freivalds-style spot checks instead of bitwise match, would allow MMA tensor cores
+3. **Model-size-aware dispatch** — dp4a for 3B (fast enough), mmvq for 27B (only option)
+4. **Better hardware** — A100/H100 have more dp4a throughput relative to MMA gap
+
